1
00:00:00,370 --> 00:00:02,270
Gosh.

2
00:00:02,340 --> 00:00:03,780
(Episode 79)

3
00:00:03,840 --> 00:00:06,750
- I told you to let me go!
- This wench is crazy.

4
00:00:08,150 --> 00:00:10,520
Seriously!

5
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:12,350
- This darn...
- Gosh...

6
00:00:12,650 --> 00:00:13,720
Unbelievable!

7
00:00:14,450 --> 00:00:15,650
Seriously!

8
00:00:16,450 --> 00:00:17,460
You've got some nerve!

9
00:00:18,660 --> 00:00:21,790
You think this is your hotel?
You're a murderer!

10
00:00:28,570 --> 00:00:30,500
Hey, I think she fainted.

11
00:00:30,700 --> 00:00:33,810
- Passed out? Yes, right. Toss her there.
- Okay.

12
00:00:33,870 --> 00:00:35,670
Gosh...

13
00:00:50,960 --> 00:00:52,260
I'm here to see the Chairman.

14
00:00:52,490 --> 00:00:56,160
Grandfather won't see you, Manager Lee.
Please leave.

15
00:00:56,230 --> 00:00:59,660
We can't have my husband's blood pressure
spiking again.

16
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:01,130
Let him in!

17
00:01:18,380 --> 00:01:19,380
Chairman.

18
00:01:20,490 --> 00:01:21,890
Please, you have to save CEO Chae.

19
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:24,960
And how am I supposed to do that?

20
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:28,760
If she committed a crime,
she'll be punished for it.

21
00:01:29,890 --> 00:01:32,830
- If not, she'll be released.
- No, sir.

22
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:35,730
You have the power to save CEO Chae.

23
00:01:36,630 --> 00:01:39,070
CEO Chae is being framed. She's innocent.

24
00:01:39,140 --> 00:01:42,340
That's for the police to determine.

25
00:01:42,440 --> 00:01:47,050
Sir, CEO Chae is Seo Rin's mother.

26
00:01:47,210 --> 00:01:50,880
For Seo Rin's sake,
she can't be branded a murderer.

27
00:01:50,950 --> 00:01:52,020
Listen here, you punk.

28
00:01:54,490 --> 00:01:57,790
You think I haven't thought of that?

29
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:00,530
Where do you get the nerve?

30
00:02:00,690 --> 00:02:03,960
Who are you to meddle in our business?
Know your place!

31
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:07,000
- I was out of line.
- And just who are you?

32
00:02:07,770 --> 00:02:10,740
What are you to CEO Chae?

33
00:02:11,170 --> 00:02:14,740
Why are you so worked up
and acting so recklessly?

34
00:02:15,070 --> 00:02:17,210
I'm sorry, Chairman. But...

35
00:02:18,510 --> 00:02:20,880
I'm afraid the longer this drags on,
the worse it will get for her.

36
00:02:21,850 --> 00:02:24,350
That's why I'm being so forward,
even at the risk of being rude.

37
00:02:25,350 --> 00:02:27,450
Besides, it's having a huge impact
on the company's stock price.

38
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:29,890
Of all the arrogant punks...

39
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:34,290
You punk, do you think I'm less worried
about the company than you are?

40
00:02:34,830 --> 00:02:37,860
There's a time and a place for everything!

41
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:39,760
Get out! Now!

42
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:48,040
Honey, your blood pressure.
Watch your blood pressure.

43
00:02:56,950 --> 00:02:57,950
Let me go.

44
00:03:02,550 --> 00:03:03,560
Shut up!

45
00:03:07,260 --> 00:03:08,290
Chae Hwa Young.

46
00:03:08,290 --> 00:03:11,830
After you stole my child from me
and killed Bok Gil,

47
00:03:12,460 --> 00:03:14,630
did you really think
you could live happily ever after?

48
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:17,140
You're more evil than a monster,
you wench.

49
00:03:25,210 --> 00:03:26,210
Please...

50
00:03:37,290 --> 00:03:38,290
Please...

51
00:03:38,890 --> 00:03:41,090
- Please...
- Help me...

52
00:03:41,460 --> 00:03:42,530
Please, help me.

53
00:03:43,660 --> 00:03:47,030
I had no choice.
I had to do it to survive!

54
00:03:48,470 --> 00:03:49,470
What do you mean, you had no choice?

55
00:03:52,940 --> 00:03:55,710
If you let me live,
I'll give you back the child.

56
00:03:57,040 --> 00:03:59,840
Do you think
I wanted to take one of the twins?

57
00:04:01,050 --> 00:04:03,350
It was the situation!
The situation made me do it!

58
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:06,620
I didn't intend for any of this to happen.

59
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:10,190
You think you wouldn't have done the same
if you were in my shoes?

60
00:04:10,460 --> 00:04:12,220
You would've done the exact same thing!

61
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:13,930
Shut up!

62
00:04:14,690 --> 00:04:15,690
Shut up!

63
00:04:20,330 --> 00:04:22,100
- Please, please!
- Shut up!

64
00:04:24,140 --> 00:04:28,570
Get out of my sight. Just disappear!
That's the only way!

65
00:04:29,670 --> 00:04:30,680
Die!

66
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:33,440
No...

67
00:04:52,330 --> 00:04:55,530
Hey, she's still out of it. Water.

68
00:05:07,110 --> 00:05:09,710
Oh, please. Don't. Please.

69
00:05:09,950 --> 00:05:12,280
Hey! She said "don't."

70
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:16,190
That just means she wants more, right?

71
00:05:16,620 --> 00:05:20,930
- Go, go. Give her a good soak.
- Go, go.

72
00:05:24,830 --> 00:05:27,630
What the heck do you think you're doing?

73
00:05:28,530 --> 00:05:29,970
I'm getting out of here.

74
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:32,000
Dream is the kingdom
I worked so hard to build.

75
00:05:32,240 --> 00:05:36,170
I will not be broken. Never!

76
00:05:36,440 --> 00:05:37,510
Never!

77
00:05:43,150 --> 00:05:44,880
Jun Ho left early this morning.

78
00:05:45,420 --> 00:05:47,790
The company's in crisis mode, apparently.

79
00:05:48,350 --> 00:05:49,590
Well, of course it is.

80
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:52,790
All the employees are paying the price
for the mess CEO Chae made.

81
00:05:54,660 --> 00:05:55,660
I'm heading out.

82
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:05,970
Jun Ho should get things back on track,

83
00:06:07,070 --> 00:06:10,510
but I despise CEO Chae more and more.
Something's just not right.

84
00:06:14,050 --> 00:06:15,250
Jun Ho and Baek Ho.

85
00:06:17,220 --> 00:06:19,520
I wanted to erase the pain
of their abandonment,

86
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:23,920
so I tried so hard
to raise them to be happy.

87
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:31,060
This is tearing me apart.
Why is this happening to us?

88
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:35,200
The fact that Jun Ho and Baek Ho are
so well-adjusted...

89
00:06:36,430 --> 00:06:38,140
is all thanks to you.

90
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:42,570
Jun Ho was older when he came to us,
so he has his demons,

91
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:45,580
but look how well Baek Ho turned out.

92
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:48,410
That's all thanks to your hard work.

93
00:06:49,150 --> 00:06:50,210
Honey.

94
00:06:51,250 --> 00:06:54,420
It means the world to me
that you see that.

95
00:06:55,890 --> 00:07:00,890
People always say how hard it must be
to raise someone else's children,

96
00:07:02,030 --> 00:07:05,160
but I've never once regretted it.

97
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:08,330
I know, Young Ja.

98
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:11,800
What's with calling me
by my name all of a sudden?

99
00:07:15,340 --> 00:07:17,070
I'm so sorry. I really am.

100
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:22,250
- For what?
- I've done something terrible to you.

101
00:07:22,710 --> 00:07:25,620
- I'm sorry.
- Don't be silly. Why so dramatic?

102
00:07:28,420 --> 00:07:29,990
If this is about us taking in the boys,

103
00:07:31,290 --> 00:07:32,760
I've never blamed you for that.

104
00:07:34,330 --> 00:07:36,530
They may not be my own flesh and blood,

105
00:07:37,060 --> 00:07:38,760
but I've cherished them so much,

106
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:43,300
and they've brought us so much joy.

107
00:07:44,940 --> 00:07:47,670
If anything, I should be thanking you.

108
00:07:51,010 --> 00:07:54,010
Kang Nam Bong. You pathetic fool.

109
00:07:54,380 --> 00:07:58,980
I happily did her bidding, not realizing
she was using me, and I caused a death.

110
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:01,720
I deserve whatever's coming to me.

111
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:11,330
What is this slop?
Hey, that wench's food is mine.

112
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:14,230
Hey, new face. I'm taking some of yours.

113
00:08:20,910 --> 00:08:21,910
This is mine.

114
00:08:23,070 --> 00:08:26,710
This wench looks like she needs
to be taught a lesson.

115
00:08:27,210 --> 00:08:28,210
Hey!

116
00:08:28,980 --> 00:08:29,980
Hey!

117
00:08:30,620 --> 00:08:34,220
Eat it. I said, eat it! Eat!
You hear me? Eat it!

118
00:08:34,650 --> 00:08:35,720
What's going on here?

119
00:08:38,860 --> 00:08:43,060
Our new face here used to be
a famous cover girl, you know.

120
00:08:43,530 --> 00:08:45,330
I was just getting to see
the legend in the flesh.

121
00:08:47,370 --> 00:08:48,570
Break it up, everyone!

122
00:08:51,770 --> 00:08:53,400
Inmate 6620, you have a visitor.

123
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:13,360
Oh Jang Mi!

124
00:09:14,760 --> 00:09:15,760
Oh Jang Mi.

125
00:09:17,060 --> 00:09:20,260
Did you come here to gloat
and see the mess I'm in?

126
00:09:21,300 --> 00:09:25,470
- When I get out, you're dead.
- Shut your mouth.

127
00:09:25,740 --> 00:09:29,110
- Inmate 6620.
- My name is Chae Hwa Young!

128
00:09:30,980 --> 00:09:32,880
Looks like prison life
doesn't agree with you.

129
00:09:33,410 --> 00:09:36,410
Your face is a wreck.
Look at the state of you.

130
00:09:36,810 --> 00:09:38,680
And you call yourself Chae Hwa Young?

131
00:09:38,980 --> 00:09:39,980
Oh Jang Mi.

132
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:41,820
How dare you mock me?

133
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:47,630
- We'll see how long you get to laugh.
- Let's do that.

134
00:09:47,990 --> 00:09:50,460
I'm not scared. And you know why?

135
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:52,400
Because you're never getting out of there.

136
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:54,800
You little rat, how dare you sneak around,
search my office,

137
00:09:55,570 --> 00:09:58,040
and stab me in the back with your lies!

138
00:09:58,140 --> 00:10:01,340
You're one to talk about backstabbing.
Always a step ahead of me, Chae Hwa Young.

139
00:10:01,410 --> 00:10:03,510
Am I wrong? Think about it.

140
00:10:03,870 --> 00:10:06,780
You came to my family
pretending to be kind and caring,

141
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:09,910
fed us sweet lies to gain our trust,
and then you stabbed us in the back.

142
00:10:09,980 --> 00:10:11,780
- Shut up!
- And that's not all, is it?

143
00:10:11,780 --> 00:10:13,320
You're the reason my dad died.

144
00:10:13,380 --> 00:10:16,120
You got Seo Rin hurt,
and look what you did to my mother.

145
00:10:16,990 --> 00:10:19,090
Chae Hwa Young,

146
00:10:19,620 --> 00:10:21,990
your life is going to be
a living nightmare.

147
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:25,030
You should just pray for a death sentence
to put you out of your misery.

148
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:29,400
Pray? You've been a fool this whole time,
but I guess you finally got one win.

149
00:10:30,030 --> 00:10:32,240
Let's see how long
you get to feel so smug.

150
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:34,340
Don't kid yourself, Oh Jang Mi.

151
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:39,280
You think I'm going to rot in here
because you want me to? In your dreams.

152
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:43,810
Sure, Chae Hwa Young.
Go ahead and run your mouth all you want.

153
00:10:44,250 --> 00:10:47,450
You acted nice while you humiliated
my family and played me for a fool.

154
00:10:47,820 --> 00:10:49,920
I'll be the bigger person
and let that slide.

155
00:10:50,420 --> 00:10:54,460
But getting my father killed?
That's something I can never forgive.

156
00:10:55,230 --> 00:10:58,860
Chae Hwa Young,
you're going to get what you deserve,

157
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:03,230
- in this life and the next.
- You can't beat me.

158
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:06,670
I swear I'm getting out of here.

159
00:11:07,300 --> 00:11:08,310
Mark my words.

160
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:11,980
Is that so?

161
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:15,480
Oh Jang Mi, you need to think
about the consequences.

162
00:11:15,850 --> 00:11:16,850
Listen.

163
00:11:17,450 --> 00:11:20,850
If I go down, you're coming with me.
You should know that.

164
00:11:20,950 --> 00:11:23,320
I've already died once.
I have nothing left to fear.

165
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:25,820
Fine, think whatever you want.

166
00:11:27,220 --> 00:11:29,790
I've really enjoyed
seeing you in this state.

167
00:11:30,490 --> 00:11:32,600
You have no idea how long
I've waited for this day.

168
00:11:33,260 --> 00:11:37,130
- My dad must be smiling down from above.
- Shut up, Oh Jang Mi.

169
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:38,740
I'll come visit again
whenever I'm bored...

170
00:11:39,770 --> 00:11:41,440
for the sight of you trapped behind bars.

171
00:11:42,540 --> 00:11:45,210
I should pack a picnic basket,
like I'm visiting an animal at the zoo.

172
00:11:45,810 --> 00:11:47,010
You can stay locked up in there...

173
00:11:47,580 --> 00:11:50,310
and keep telling yourself
you're going to get out.

174
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:56,650
Oh Jang Mi!
How dare you say such things to me?

175
00:11:58,660 --> 00:12:01,560
Just you wait.
I won't let you get away with this.

176
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:06,400
No, sir, that's not what I mean.

177
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:14,140
Yes. I know the hotel's image
has hit rock bottom,

178
00:12:14,770 --> 00:12:18,840
but it'll bounce right back once our CEO
is cleared of all charges. Don't worry.

179
00:12:19,980 --> 00:12:24,010
Also, we're currently preparing
for an affiliates' conference.

180
00:12:24,180 --> 00:12:27,150
General Manager Kang, that's enough.
We're terminating our contract.

181
00:12:27,220 --> 00:12:29,290
Sir, wait!

182
00:12:31,460 --> 00:12:33,420
Looks like you're busy
doing damage control.

183
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:35,890
What is it?
Are they pulling out of the contract?

184
00:12:37,190 --> 00:12:39,500
Yes. But what brings you here?

185
00:12:41,830 --> 00:12:45,400
I went to visit CEO Chae.

186
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:49,540
And how is she doing?

187
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:52,580
Something about
what Baek Ho said felt off,

188
00:12:53,940 --> 00:12:56,610
and I wanted to see her
to get some straight answers.

189
00:12:58,120 --> 00:13:02,050
But Director Ma was already there.
I couldn't get in to see her.

190
00:13:02,690 --> 00:13:07,220
- I see.
- Is Baek Ho CEO Chae's legal counsel?

191
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:08,930
What are you talking about?

192
00:13:09,430 --> 00:13:14,330
It looked like he came with Director Ma.
I saw Baek Ho's car in the parking lot.

193
00:13:15,100 --> 00:13:16,100
What?

194
00:13:22,010 --> 00:13:23,110
What did Chae Hwa Young say?

195
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:26,440
She said she'll come after me
when she gets out.

196
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:28,580
She was as fiery as ever.

197
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:30,080
She'll realize the truth soon enough.

198
00:13:30,610 --> 00:13:33,580
The crucial evidence is too clear
for her to get away.

199
00:13:34,790 --> 00:13:36,850
You haven't told the Chairman yet,
have you?

200
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:40,560
I don't want to shock him,
so I think I should tell him later.

201
00:13:41,860 --> 00:13:42,930
But there's something...

202
00:13:43,530 --> 00:13:45,160
I have to do as Ma Seo Rin.

203
00:13:46,460 --> 00:13:48,430
- What is it?
- The ones who kidnapped my mother...

204
00:13:48,430 --> 00:13:50,170
and handed her over to Chae Hwa Young...

205
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:51,870
were Yeom San Wol and Jin Hong Ju.

206
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:54,270
What? How could they do that
to your sick mother?

207
00:13:56,340 --> 00:13:58,780
Those two are absolute monsters.

208
00:13:59,940 --> 00:14:01,050
I have to take it all back.

209
00:14:01,350 --> 00:14:04,280
You need to apologize to the victim
and issue a public apology.

210
00:14:04,350 --> 00:14:06,180
You need to take proper measures.

211
00:14:07,850 --> 00:14:10,120
As for your one percent share
in the company,

212
00:14:10,790 --> 00:14:14,830
- it will be transferred to Yeom San Wol.
- Honey! You're finally giving me...

213
00:14:18,130 --> 00:14:21,400
So, Yeom San Wol
has that one percent share...

214
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:22,700
she got from Chairman Ma a while back,

215
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,400
and you want to take it from her, right?

216
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:28,240
Yes. That woman doesn't deserve
to own any Dream Group shares.

217
00:14:28,610 --> 00:14:29,610
An eye for an eye.

218
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:32,440
Dear.

219
00:14:32,740 --> 00:14:35,010
Look who's here.
It's been a while, you two.

220
00:14:35,010 --> 00:14:37,650
Our vegetables and seafood are very fresh,

221
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:38,750
so please, eat up.

222
00:14:39,380 --> 00:14:40,380
Thanks, we will.

223
00:14:45,660 --> 00:14:46,660
But...

224
00:14:46,860 --> 00:14:50,360
I just have no idea
how to get those shares from Yeom San Wol.

225
00:14:50,460 --> 00:14:52,400
I have an idea.

226
00:14:53,760 --> 00:14:55,530
It's dropped 12 percent today alone.

227
00:14:55,830 --> 00:14:58,470
Foreign investors are about to start
dumping their shares.

228
00:14:58,900 --> 00:15:02,010
You need to announce the CEO's dismissal
within the next few days.

229
00:15:02,870 --> 00:15:03,870
Listen.

230
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:06,610
I need you to go to the detention center.

231
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:10,580
Tell CEO Chae if she has a conscience,
she should give up her shares...

232
00:15:10,950 --> 00:15:12,350
to help stabilize the situation.

233
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:16,520
And leak to the press that the CEO
is taking full responsibility...

234
00:15:16,590 --> 00:15:18,420
and is considering donating
her personal assets.

235
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:19,720
If we do that,

236
00:15:20,290 --> 00:15:21,860
the stock price will bounce back.

237
00:15:22,360 --> 00:15:25,060
Yes, Chairman.
I'll schedule a visit immediately.

238
00:15:25,930 --> 00:15:27,130
Give up her shares?

239
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:35,270
Get this re-approved.

240
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:39,080
Gosh, that felt good.

241
00:15:39,380 --> 00:15:42,010
After all I've had to take
from CEO Chae over the years?

242
00:15:43,110 --> 00:15:44,880
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

243
00:15:45,950 --> 00:15:47,150
Hey, Hong Ju?

244
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:51,160
- Yes, Mother. What is it?
- Why so formal all of a sudden?

245
00:15:51,420 --> 00:15:53,590
What's gotten into you?
Are you feeling okay?

246
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:57,460
Mom, I've been thinking.

247
00:15:57,460 --> 00:15:59,830
CEO Chae will either get life in prison
for murder.

248
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:01,970
or even if she hires a team
of high-powered lawyers,

249
00:16:02,230 --> 00:16:04,300
she's looking at a minimum of ten years.

250
00:16:04,740 --> 00:16:07,670
So, who do you think
will take over Dream Hotel?

251
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:10,470
That's what I've been trying
to tell you, sweetie.

252
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:14,180
The Chairman just told Secretary Kim
to go visit her at the detention center.

253
00:16:14,550 --> 00:16:17,210
I think he's going to take
Hwa Young's shares...

254
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:19,220
and give them to me.

255
00:16:19,350 --> 00:16:22,550
Really? So with that plus the one percent
you already have,

256
00:16:22,890 --> 00:16:24,220
how much will you own in total?

257
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:28,260
Mom, at this rate, you could become
a major shareholder in Dream Hotel!

258
00:16:29,930 --> 00:16:33,360
Mom, let's not tell the Chairman
that Ma Seo Rin has a twin.

259
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:35,530
It sounds like they already know
about the twin.

260
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:38,570
What do you mean by saying
we shouldn’t mention the twin?

261
00:16:38,670 --> 00:16:42,510
Think about it. It means one more person
to share the Dream Group fortune with.

262
00:16:42,670 --> 00:16:44,840
- How is that good for us?
- You've got a point.

263
00:16:45,640 --> 00:16:47,110
My clever girl.

264
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:51,620
So that means my Hong Ju is going to be
the CEO of Dream Hotel.

265
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:52,980
CEO Jin Hong Ju?

266
00:16:54,390 --> 00:16:56,050
I like the sound of that.

267
00:16:57,590 --> 00:16:58,620
Hey, Jang Mi.

268
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:01,490
Thankfully, Mom's doing okay.

269
00:17:04,030 --> 00:17:06,860
But I'm still furious at that awful woman,
Yeom San Wol.

270
00:17:07,530 --> 00:17:09,270
Absolutely. She needs to pay
for what she did.

271
00:17:12,040 --> 00:17:14,370
So that's the plan?

272
00:17:15,870 --> 00:17:16,870
Got it.

273
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:21,450
Tae Pyung, I miss Jang Mi.

274
00:17:22,080 --> 00:17:26,350
- When is Jang Mi coming home?
- Uncle, I miss her too.

275
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:27,480
Easy, easy.

276
00:17:27,820 --> 00:17:31,560
You'll see her all you want soon enough,
so for now, just settle down.

277
00:17:36,630 --> 00:17:39,530
Before Oh Jang Mi spills everything
to Chairman Ma,

278
00:17:39,660 --> 00:17:40,730
I have to get out of here.

279
00:17:41,670 --> 00:17:45,570
What the heck is Manager Lee doing?
Why haven't I heard a word from him?

280
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:47,440
Gosh.

281
00:17:48,570 --> 00:17:49,570
Hey.

282
00:17:49,870 --> 00:17:52,380
Gosh, look at you,
acting like you're about to collapse.

283
00:17:53,180 --> 00:17:55,850
Hey, you murderer. You killed someone,

284
00:17:55,910 --> 00:17:58,720
and you think
you can just sit here all comfortable?

285
00:17:59,350 --> 00:18:03,890
I'm innocent. I've never killed anyone.
I didn't do anything wrong!

286
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:06,160
You think you're the only one
who's been wronged?

287
00:18:08,030 --> 00:18:11,200
Every single person in here
claims they're innocent.

288
00:18:11,560 --> 00:18:13,960
- What a bunch of nonsense.
- Hey!

289
00:18:14,630 --> 00:18:17,370
Just do the laundry already.

290
00:18:17,430 --> 00:18:19,670
What are you going to do
about all this laundry?

291
00:18:20,370 --> 00:18:21,370
Me?

292
00:18:24,210 --> 00:18:25,210
"Me?"

293
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:29,550
She still doesn't get it. "Me?" she says.

294
00:18:29,910 --> 00:18:31,380
My goodness.

295
00:18:31,620 --> 00:18:35,220
Then who else is going to do it?
You're the newbie, so who do you think?

296
00:18:35,290 --> 00:18:36,550
You have to do it.

297
00:18:36,820 --> 00:18:40,060
- Good grief.
- Seriously, what do we do with her?

298
00:18:40,390 --> 00:18:43,190
You're the one who has to do it. Who else?

299
00:18:43,530 --> 00:18:47,600
- She still doesn't get it.
- Guard!

300
00:18:47,660 --> 00:18:48,800
- Come on!
- Guard!

301
00:18:48,870 --> 00:18:50,200
A guard? Please.

302
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:52,500
I heard that when you were out there,

303
00:18:52,500 --> 00:18:56,170
you walked all over people just like this.

304
00:18:56,310 --> 00:19:00,110
So? How does it feel to get a taste
of your own medicine? Do you like it?

305
00:19:00,180 --> 00:19:02,010
- Do you like it?
- Stop.

306
00:19:03,080 --> 00:19:05,720
- "Stop?"
- Did you ever even see us as people?

307
00:19:05,880 --> 00:19:09,750
Step on her! What are you waiting for?
Let's teach this one a lesson!

308
00:19:10,020 --> 00:19:13,360
We need to teach her a lesson!

309
00:19:15,030 --> 00:19:18,000
- Step on her!
- This is exhausting.

310
00:19:18,560 --> 00:19:19,560
Class dismissed for today.

311
00:19:23,630 --> 00:19:24,640
That was tiring.

312
00:19:32,080 --> 00:19:33,840
I'll kill every single one of them.

313
00:19:34,810 --> 00:19:36,080
I won't let them get away with this.

314
00:19:38,080 --> 00:19:39,520
I'll make every last one of them pay.

315
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:42,990
Hey, look.

316
00:19:43,190 --> 00:19:44,560
She's crying.

317
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:46,620
So pathetic.

318
00:19:46,890 --> 00:19:49,360
Oh my, are you crying?

319
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:51,930
Go on and cry all you want.

320
00:19:52,330 --> 00:19:53,530
What do you mean, "cry all you want?"

321
00:19:55,930 --> 00:19:58,070
Stop crying and get a grip.

322
00:20:01,870 --> 00:20:03,870
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

323
00:20:05,780 --> 00:20:08,750
Tae Pyung, now's your chance. Go for it.

324
00:20:12,280 --> 00:20:15,220
Special event!
Massive sale at Suk Hee's Side Dish Shop.

325
00:20:15,650 --> 00:20:18,660
For 3 days starting today,
get 3 side dishes for 10 dollars.

326
00:20:19,190 --> 00:20:21,590
San Wol, don't miss out on this chance.

327
00:20:21,930 --> 00:20:24,360
I thought of you in particular,
so I wanted to let you know.

328
00:20:27,300 --> 00:20:28,370
Goodness.

329
00:20:29,070 --> 00:20:32,440
- Why so jumpy?
- It's nothing.

330
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:37,670
You haven't had much of an appetite
lately because of CEO Chae, honey.

331
00:20:37,870 --> 00:20:41,210
So I'll run to the side dish shop
to get you something.

332
00:20:41,850 --> 00:20:43,050
All right, you do that.

333
00:20:54,220 --> 00:20:58,260
She said she was going to buy side dishes,
so why did she just run into the bedroom?

334
00:21:00,060 --> 00:21:02,270
Tae Pyung finally said my name.

335
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:03,930
He said he was thinking of me,
specifically.

336
00:21:04,770 --> 00:21:05,870
What do I do?

337
00:21:06,470 --> 00:21:07,570
My heart's racing.

338
00:21:08,510 --> 00:21:11,480
Finally, Tae Pyung's starting
to think about me too.

339
00:21:14,510 --> 00:21:18,220
I guess it's true what they say.
Persistence pays off.

340
00:21:19,780 --> 00:21:20,980
Now, what should I wear to go see him?

341
00:21:25,390 --> 00:21:26,390
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

342
00:21:29,690 --> 00:21:31,560
Are you serious?

343
00:21:32,230 --> 00:21:34,800
That's amazing!
Talk about hitting the jackpot.

344
00:21:37,170 --> 00:21:40,700
- Jackpot?
- I came into a little money today,

345
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:44,840
but if I had a bit more money,
this could have been my big break.

346
00:21:45,240 --> 00:21:47,980
What a shame.
After you make all that money,

347
00:21:48,110 --> 00:21:49,680
don't you dare pretend you don't know me.

348
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:50,780
Bye.

349
00:21:54,180 --> 00:21:56,450
You're here, San Wol.

350
00:21:58,660 --> 00:21:59,660
Tae Pyung.

351
00:22:01,190 --> 00:22:02,430
Who was that on the phone?

352
00:22:02,990 --> 00:22:04,230
It sounded like they hit the jackpot.

353
00:22:04,360 --> 00:22:08,300
My friend got into crypto
and made a thousand times his investment.

354
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:11,370
I just downloaded the app he told me about
and only put in 5,000 dollars...

355
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:14,340
- and I'm making 500 dollars a day.
- You put in 5,000, and making 500 a day?

356
00:22:15,010 --> 00:22:18,140
- Wait, there's something that lucrative?
- It's easy money.

357
00:22:18,580 --> 00:22:21,240
But he's pulling in
an astronomical amount,

358
00:22:21,850 --> 00:22:23,710
so honestly, even though he's my friend,
I'm pretty jealous.

359
00:22:23,910 --> 00:22:27,080
My goodness.
Is that sort of thing for real?

360
00:22:27,780 --> 00:22:31,320
- So what is it?
- Come on, San Wol.

361
00:22:31,820 --> 00:22:33,460
You can't jump in.

362
00:22:33,460 --> 00:22:35,490
It's for experienced young people
who know what they're doing.

363
00:22:35,560 --> 00:22:38,900
Hey, what are you talking about?
Age is just a number.

364
00:22:39,030 --> 00:22:42,570
You have no idea how young I am.
I may look this way outside, but inside,

365
00:22:43,370 --> 00:22:45,500
I'm still a teenager at heart.

366
00:22:46,870 --> 00:22:50,640
Of course. And you look very young
on the outside, too, San Wol.

367
00:22:51,040 --> 00:22:54,680
- So, come on, let me in on it.
- Well...

368
00:22:55,110 --> 00:22:57,650
But there is risk involved.

369
00:22:57,710 --> 00:23:00,650
Come on, Tae Pyung.
You're really underestimating me.

370
00:23:00,980 --> 00:23:03,720
I know my way around a bank.

371
00:23:04,190 --> 00:23:06,860
High-yield investments
never guarantee your principal,

372
00:23:07,190 --> 00:23:09,160
and they always come with some risk.

373
00:23:10,330 --> 00:23:12,930
- Still...
- I said, show me.

374
00:23:13,530 --> 00:23:16,130
I haven't been able to find a good place
to invest my money lately,

375
00:23:16,430 --> 00:23:18,570
so I was just about to start
looking into things anyway.

376
00:23:20,940 --> 00:23:24,610
Okay, but if you end up losing money,
I can't be held responsible.

377
00:23:24,980 --> 00:23:26,840
You can't blame me, all right?

378
00:23:27,110 --> 00:23:30,380
Of course.
Besides, why would I lose money?

379
00:23:30,610 --> 00:23:33,420
I'm not some fool.

380
00:23:34,620 --> 00:23:38,050
Now, just tell me the name of it.
I want to know what this is all about.

381
00:23:38,720 --> 00:23:39,760
Well,

382
00:23:40,590 --> 00:23:41,960
it's a new crypto coin,

383
00:23:42,730 --> 00:23:46,600
and it uses AI to do arbitrage trading
with crypto assets.

384
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:47,900
I see.

385
00:23:48,470 --> 00:23:49,870
Artificial intelligence?

386
00:23:50,930 --> 00:23:51,940
You mean, like a robot?

387
00:23:52,470 --> 00:23:54,600
- Yes.
- I knew it!

388
00:24:02,880 --> 00:24:03,880
Boss.

389
00:24:04,510 --> 00:24:05,680
You're the only one who can do it.

390
00:24:06,520 --> 00:24:08,150
What do you mean by that?

391
00:24:09,420 --> 00:24:11,820
You're the only one
with a connection to Oh Bok Gil.

392
00:24:12,690 --> 00:24:14,160
You're taking the fall for CEO Chae.

393
00:24:14,490 --> 00:24:16,730
Boss, you can't be serious.

394
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:19,960
I don't want to go to prison.

395
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:23,070
This is a down payment.

396
00:24:24,170 --> 00:24:25,300
When CEO Chae gets out,

397
00:24:25,900 --> 00:24:27,170
I'll give you
another bag of cash just like this.

398
00:24:28,840 --> 00:24:30,110
And you already know this.

399
00:24:30,770 --> 00:24:32,410
CEO Chae has connections in high places.

400
00:24:33,940 --> 00:24:35,650
I've already laid all the groundwork.

401
00:24:37,010 --> 00:24:40,320
If you turn yourself in,
CEO Chae will get out right away,

402
00:24:41,820 --> 00:24:43,490
and I'll continue to have your back.

403
00:24:45,690 --> 00:24:47,390
You'll get out easily too.

404
00:24:50,030 --> 00:24:51,130
And look,

405
00:24:51,530 --> 00:24:53,760
don't you think it's time
your girl stopped struggling?

406
00:24:54,360 --> 00:24:56,070
You could have kids
that look just like you.

407
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,670
Hey, how long are you going to waste
your life doing these piddly jobs?

408
00:25:02,310 --> 00:25:05,040
What if the arrangements
you've made fall through?

409
00:25:07,780 --> 00:25:09,650
Have we only been working together
for a day or two?

410
00:25:10,580 --> 00:25:11,950
Are you saying you don't trust me?

411
00:25:13,820 --> 00:25:14,890
No, that's not it, Boss.

412
00:25:16,220 --> 00:25:17,820
A major law firm will take your case.

413
00:25:18,390 --> 00:25:19,820
Just do exactly what the lawyer tells you.

414
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:29,500
Let's get this over with.

415
00:25:37,440 --> 00:25:39,810
They say you can make
at least a tenfold return.

416
00:25:41,710 --> 00:25:42,750
Ten times?

417
00:25:42,750 --> 00:25:44,050
So if I put in 100,000 dollars,
I get one million.

418
00:25:44,050 --> 00:25:46,620
If I put in a million, ten million?

419
00:25:48,890 --> 00:25:50,290
If that happens,

420
00:25:50,790 --> 00:25:54,320
I can leave that old geezer
and be with the young, vibrant Tae Pyung.

421
00:25:54,590 --> 00:25:56,490
I could start a whole new life.

422
00:26:02,070 --> 00:26:04,400
- Tae Pyung.
- San Wol.

423
00:26:04,770 --> 00:26:07,840
You know, I'm starting to think
I shouldn't have told you about this.

424
00:26:08,170 --> 00:26:09,940
If you don't have the money,
just forget about it.

425
00:26:10,040 --> 00:26:12,140
Gosh, what do you mean I don't have money?

426
00:26:12,340 --> 00:26:16,510
It's just tied up in Dream Group stock,
so I'm not very liquid at the moment.

427
00:26:16,610 --> 00:26:18,950
I see, so you have it
in Dream Group stock.

428
00:26:19,720 --> 00:26:21,320
My friend is cash-rich...

429
00:26:21,320 --> 00:26:22,720
and actually
does stock-for-cash exchanges.

430
00:26:23,120 --> 00:26:27,160
- How about I set up a meeting for you?
- You'd do that?

431
00:26:27,890 --> 00:26:29,830
Yes, please, Tae Pyung.

432
00:26:30,630 --> 00:26:31,960
Let's do it.
Strike while the iron's hot, right?

433
00:26:31,960 --> 00:26:33,000
Let's meet now.

434
00:26:33,160 --> 00:26:37,300
You can bring your friend,
and I can cash out immediately.

435
00:26:38,300 --> 00:26:40,800
I've got to get in on this jackpot.
I can't wait.

436
00:26:41,100 --> 00:26:43,070
Okay, shall we, then?

437
00:26:46,210 --> 00:26:47,210
San Wol.

438
00:26:47,840 --> 00:26:50,910
If you hit the jackpot,
you'll take me to Thailand, right?

439
00:26:52,050 --> 00:26:54,350
I've never been to Thailand, you know.

440
00:26:55,090 --> 00:26:57,090
Of course! And why stop at Thailand?

441
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:59,590
We could even go to Hong Kong.

442
00:27:07,460 --> 00:27:10,470
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

443
00:27:11,870 --> 00:27:14,370
She took the bait. Let's move.

444
00:27:22,780 --> 00:27:24,410
- My stomach.
- My gosh.

445
00:27:24,410 --> 00:27:25,520
Oh, dear.

446
00:27:26,180 --> 00:27:27,920
There, I think that's him.

447
00:27:50,940 --> 00:27:53,940
- Hi, Tae Pyung.
- James. Over here!

448
00:27:54,980 --> 00:27:56,780
- What's up?
- What's up, man?

449
00:27:59,150 --> 00:28:00,180
I'm sorry.

450
00:28:03,920 --> 00:28:06,520
- Nice to meet you.
- Right...

451
00:28:10,390 --> 00:28:11,430
Hello.

452
00:28:12,060 --> 00:28:13,060
I'm...

453
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:15,300
James Park.

454
00:28:16,300 --> 00:28:17,500
Yes.

455
00:28:37,890 --> 00:28:39,520
(The First Man)

456
00:28:39,690 --> 00:28:42,460
Look at the state of your face.
Why are you just letting them hit you?

457
00:28:42,630 --> 00:28:44,590
You abandoned me, just to live like this?

458
00:28:44,590 --> 00:28:46,760
So I could see you in this pathetic state?

459
00:28:46,900 --> 00:28:48,630
Wait! Just hear me out.

460
00:28:48,930 --> 00:28:52,240
Once I get out of here,
I'll give all of you jobs at my hotel.

461
00:28:52,440 --> 00:28:54,900
You have my word. Let's make a deal.

462
00:28:54,940 --> 00:28:57,340
It's time for the real Oh Jang Mi
to come out.

463
00:28:57,340 --> 00:28:59,010
I want to go back to my rightful place.

464
00:28:59,410 --> 00:29:01,910
Grandfather, it's Seo Rin.

465
00:29:04,010 --> 00:29:06,020
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
